# ShellCheck config for conduck-connect — public on purpose, so an auditor sees
# exactly what is suppressed and why. CI runs `shellcheck --severity=warning`,
# which also drops info-level SC2015 ("A && B || C is not if-then-else") on the
# handful of intentional best-effort status lines.
#
# SC2034 (unused variable): a few benign dead/reserved assignments in the
#   feature-frozen, live-verified wizard (FUNNEL_PORTS_RE, local_port, ts_ok,
#   FS_REUSED). Harmless; suppressed rather than refactoring a frozen script.
# SC2155 (declare and assign separately): the single site is a `printf | base64`
#   pipe whose return value cannot fail meaningfully.
disable=SC2034,SC2155
